# Unitas-GridFlow — Cursor Rules

## First action — read this before anything else
Read: `AI_CONTROL/00_MASTER_SOURCE_OF_TRUTH.md`
That file is the single source of truth for the entire project. It holds current test count, check-type count, rulepacks, and current priority.

## Then also read
- `AI_CONTROL/03_CURRENT_TASK.md` — what to do this session
- `AI_CONTROL/04_SESSION_HANDOFF.md` — what changed last session
- `CHANGELOG.md` — rolling history of what shipped

## Project identity
Unitas GridFlow — narrow pre-CAD QA and compliance tool for UK electricity
network survey-to-design handoffs. A DNO survey compliance gatekeeper.

Location: `/Users/noelcollins/Unitas-GridFlow/`
GitHub: `https://github.com/NoelyC123/Unitas-GridFlow`
Port: 5001 | Venv: `.venv312` | Python: 3.13

## Tech stack
Flask, pandas, geopandas, reportlab, pyproj, Leaflet, Bootstrap 5

## Hard rules (full list in master truth §7)
- Never broaden scope beyond narrow MVP.
- Always read a file before editing it — never assume contents.
- After any change: `pytest -v` (all tests must pass).
- After tests pass: `git add / commit / push`.
- Commit messages must be clear and descriptive.
- Never add features not tied to the current task.
- Never restore from `_quarantine/` blindly.
- Never treat autocomplete suggestions as authoritative for DNO-specific values.

## Key files
- `app/dno_rules.py`         — QA rulepacks (current priority: add more DNOs)
- `app/qa_engine.py`         — QA engine (check types in master truth §4)
- `app/routes/api_intake.py` — main CSV processing pipeline
- `app/routes/api_rulepacks.py` — rulepack API (stub — needs wiring)
- `tests/`                   — pytest suite, must stay green
